    "title": "Opinion Announcement - June 26, 2015 (Part 2)",
    "transcript": {
        "title": "Obergefell v. Hodges",
        "duration": 703.104,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 703.104,
                "byte_start": 0,
                "byte_stop": 0,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 703.104,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15086,
                            "name": "John G. Roberts, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/john_g_roberts_jr",
                            "last_name": "Roberts",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2730,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1127970000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2730"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32683,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 52305,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/john_g_roberts_jr_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 3702,
                            "identifier": "john_g_roberts_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 12.111,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "From the dawn of human history until a few years ago for every people known to have populated this planet, marriage was defined as the union of a man and a woman."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.111,
                                "stop": 27.844,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That is true for the Kalahari Bushmen and the Han Chinese for the Carthaginians and the Aztecs for any civilization at anytime at anyplace in the world, and certainly for those who wrote and ratified our Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.844,
                                "stop": 45.514,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But today five lawyers have ordered every State to change its definition of marriage to one that matches a new one that they favor, because those lawyers have in their words new insight and a better informed understanding of liberty, just who do we think we are."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.514,
                                "stop": 48.45,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "I have no choice but to dissent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.45,
                                "stop": 53.576,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "These cases are not about whether we think same-sex marriage is a good idea."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.576,
                                "stop": 60.652,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The petitioners make strong arguments rooted in social policy and considerations of fairness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.652,
                                "stop": 77.112,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They have moving personal stories, stories like theirs have played a major role in persuading voters and legislators in 11 states and the District of Columbia to revise their laws and adopt same-sex marriage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.112,
                                "stop": 79.83,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But this is a court, not a legislature."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.83,
                                "stop": 86.522,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Under the Constitution we have power to say what the law is not what it should be."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.522,
                                "stop": 96.517,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And while the policy arguments for extending marriage to same-sex couples may be compelling but legal arguments for requiring such an extension are not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.517,
                                "stop": 101.288,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our Constitution does not enact any one theory of marriage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.288,
                                "stop": 109.973,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The people of a State are free to expand marriage to include same-sex couples or to retain the historic definition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.973,
                                "stop": 116.814,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The majority bases its contrary decision on the due process clause of the 14th Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.814,
                                "stop": 128.994,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But allowing unelected judges to strike down democratically enacted laws based on rights that are not actually written in the Constitution raises obvious concerns about the judicial role."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.994,
                                "stop": 144.367,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That is why our precedents have insisted that judges weighing claims of such implied fundamental rights must exercise caution and restraint, and they must ground such a right firmly in our history and tradition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.367,
                                "stop": 149.028,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The court of course cannot do that with respect to same-sex marriage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 149.028,
                                "stop": 155.513,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "No one would call the Court\u0027s approach today cautious and restrained least of all the majority."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.513,
                                "stop": 163.16,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It expressly rejects what it calls any \u201cinclination to proceed with caution.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.16,
                                "stop": 185.365,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It acknowledges that on one side of today\u0027s question is the uniform practice of every civilization in human history, but on the other side, as the Court explains, there have been referenda, legislative debates and grassroot campaigns as well as countless this is a \u201cstudies, papers, books and other popular and scholarly writings.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.365,
                                "stop": 191.142,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "There has been \u201cextensive litigation in State and Federal courts\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.142,
                                "stop": 200.107,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "\u201cThis has led to an enhanced understanding of the issue, an understanding reflected in the arguments now presented for resolution by this court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 200.107,
                                "stop": 212.635,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In other words, the court is now ready to render its verdict on history and the institution that has formed a basic building block of human society since time immemorial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 212.635,
                                "stop": 218.116,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The majority relies heavily on cases recognizing a fundamental right to marry."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 218.116,
                                "stop": 224.556,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "These cases of course do not hold that anyone who wants to get married must be allowed to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 224.556,
                                "stop": 233.89,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Instead they prevent a State from restricting access to marriage as the institution of marriage has been understood throughout history."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 233.89,
                                "stop": 246.335,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Loving v. Virginia for example, struck down racial restrictions on marriage between a man and a woman, but Loving did not create any right to make a State change its definition of marriage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 246.335,
                                "stop": 253.2,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It struck down racial restrictions on who could participate in marriage as historically defined."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 253.2,
                                "stop": 262.761,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Removing racial barriers to marriage did not change what marriage was anymore than integrating schools changed what a school was."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 262.761,
                                "stop": 267.957,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Majority also cites precedents implying a fundamental right of privacy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 267.957,
                                "stop": 272.88,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But the marriage laws at issue here do not restrict privacy in any way."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 272.88,
                                "stop": 281.867,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Same-sex couples remain free to live together, to engage in intimate conduct and to raise their families as they see fit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 281.867,
                                "stop": 287.571,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "At the same the time laws in no way interfere with the right to be left alone."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 287.571,
                                "stop": 297.742,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Simply put, the privacy cases do not help petitioners because they do not seek privacy, they seek the opposite of privacy, public recognition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 297.742,
                                "stop": 303.336,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Ultimately only one precedent supports the majority\u0027s interpretation of the due process clause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 303.336,
                                "stop": 312.663,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Lochner v. New York, in that case decided in 1905 the Court struck down a State law setting maximum hours for bakery employees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 312.663,
                                "stop": 324.395,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The court did so based on its own conception of liberty in particular its view that the Constitution protects \u201ca general right of an individual to be free in his own person.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 324.395,
                                "stop": 336.06,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In the years after Lochner the Court struck down nearly 200 other similar laws that the Court saw as a \u201cinterference with the rights of the individual.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 336.06,
                                "stop": 341.96,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now the Lochner era is now regarded as one of the most unprincipled periods in the Court\u0027s history."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 341.96,
                                "stop": 353.532,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The problem with the Court\u0027s approach was not that the particular liberties the Court enshrined were undesirable but that such an unrestrained enterprise had no basis in the Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 353.532,
                                "stop": 369.037,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As Justice Oliver Wendell Holmes explained in his Lochner dissent the Constitution is not intended to embody a particular economic theory, it is instead made for people of fundamentally different views, just so here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 369.037,
                                "stop": 379.077,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Constitution is not intended to embody a particular theory of marriage because it is made for people of fundamentally different views."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 379.077,
                                "stop": 389.86,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As Justice Holmes wrote in another case the criterion of constitutionality is not whether we believe a law to be for the public good -- and so too here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 389.86,
                                "stop": 393.895,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court eventually agreed with Justice Holmes and repudiated Lochner."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 393.895,
                                "stop": 409.607,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But today we see it resurrected as the majority relies on its free-wheeling conception of individual autonomy to justify striking down the marriage laws of more than half the states and transforming an institution that has endured for millennia."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 409.607,
                                "stop": 425.723,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In the majority\u0027s view traditional marriage laws impermissibly restrict petitioner\u0027s right to \u201cdefine and express their identity and to exercise the right to personal choice regarding marriage that is inherent in the concept of individual autonomy.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 425.723,
                                "stop": 439.913,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The majority\u0027s conception of liberty echoes nothing as much as Lochner\u0027s invocation of \u201cthe right of the individual to his personal liberty or to enter into those contracts which may seem to him appropriate or necessary.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 439.913,
                                "stop": 452.734,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Like the court in Lochner which concluded that we do not believe in the soundness of the views which uphold this law, the majority today relies on its own understanding of what freedom is and must become."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 452.734,
                                "stop": 471.042,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And like the court in Lochner which believed that the interest of the public is not in the slightest degree affected by the bakery hours at issue, the majority today insists that same-sex marriage would pose no risk of harm to themselves, to the same-sex couples or third parties."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 471.042,
                                "stop": 482.448,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now the elevation of the fullest individual self realization over the constraints that society has expressed in law may or may not be attractive moral philosophy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 482.448,
                                "stop": 497.661,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But a Justice\u0027s Commission does not confer any special moral, philosophical, or social insight sufficient to justify imposing those perceptions on fellow citizens under the pretense of due process."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 497.661,
                                "stop": 503.018,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "There is indeed a process due to people on issues of this sort, the democratic process."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 503.018,
                                "stop": 512.03,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Respecting that understanding requires the court to be guided by law not any particular school or social thought."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 512.03,
                                "stop": 519.654,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now ultimately the deepest problem with the majority\u0027s decision today is the disrespect it shows to democratic process."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 519.654,
                                "stop": 527.088,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In recent years people around our country have engaged in a serious and thoughtful debate about same-sex marriage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 527.088,
                                "stop": 532.813,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Voters have cast ballots in favor or opposed and sometimes changed their minds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 532.813,
                                "stop": 542.375,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Political leaders have similarly re-examined their positions and reversed course or explained adherence to old convictions confirmed new."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 542.375,
                                "stop": 549.747,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "When decisions like this are reached through democratic means, some people will inevitably be disappointed with the results."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 549.747,
                                "stop": 559.92,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But those whose views do not prevail at least know that they have had their say and accordingly are reconciled to the result of a fair and honest debate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 559.92,
                                "stop": 566.268,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They also know that they can try again as their ideas gain acceptance and momentum elsewhere."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 566.268,
                                "stop": 574.653,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It is what happened in May where voters adopted same-sex marriage just three years after upholding the traditional definition of marriage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 574.653,
                                "stop": 577.641,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Today\u0027s decision puts a stop to all that."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 577.641,
                                "stop": 584.96,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "There will be consequences to shutting down the political process on an issue of such profound public significance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 584.96,
                                "stop": 588.224,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Closing debate tends to close minds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 588.224,
                                "stop": 596.886,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Indeed however heartened the proponents of same-sex marriage might be on this day, it is worth acknowledging what they have lost and lost forever."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 596.886,
                                "stop": 610.315,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opportunity to win the true acceptance that comes from persuading their fellow citizens of the justice of their cause, and they lose this just when the winds of change were freshening at their backs."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 610.315,
                                "stop": 615.088,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now in the face of all this a much different view of the Court\u0027s rule is possible."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 615.088,
                                "stop": 618.376,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That view is more modest and restrained."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 618.376,
                                "stop": 626.708,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It is more skeptical that the legal abilities of judges also reflect insight into moral and philosophical issues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 626.708,
                                "stop": 638.532,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It is more sensitive to the fact that judges are unelected and unaccountable and that the legitimacy of their power depends on confining into to the exercise of legal judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 638.532,
                                "stop": 669.259,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It is more attuned to the lessons of history and what is meant for the country and the court and justices have exceeded their proper bounds, and it is less pretentious than to suppose that while people around the world have viewed an institution in a particular way for thousands of years it is five lawyers on the present court who are the ones that have been chosen to burst the bonds of that history and wave life and to command that every state follow their lead."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 669.259,
                                "stop": 680.001,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now if you are among the many Americans of whatever sexual orientation who favor expanding same-sex marriage by all means celebrate today\u0027s decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 680.001,
                                "stop": 696.909,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Celebrate the achievement of a desired goal, celebrate the opportunity for a new expression of commitment to a partner, celebrate the availability of new benefits. But do not celebrate the Constitution -- it had nothing to do with it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 696.909,
                                "stop": 703.104,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "I respectfully dissent."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
